cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel algorithm for low rank matrix factorisation in recommender systems. It also involves the use of Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD) method for optimisation, which is a common technique in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as recommender systems are often used in information retrieval applications. 

Additionally, it could be categorised under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques to improve the accuracy of recommender systems. 

The paper also deals with large and sparse datasets, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves developing efficient algorithms for handling such datasets. 

Finally, it could be categorised under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as recommender systems are often used in social networks to suggest friends or content to users.
